  "prompt": "What is the condition of alcohol ban in Bihar?",
  "response": "In Bihar, a complete prohibition on alcohol was implemented in April 2016 under the leadership of Chief Minister Nitish Kumar. The state has one of the strictest alcohol ban policies in India. Key aspects of the alcohol ban include:\n\n1. Total ban on production, sale, and consumption of alcohol\n\n2. Strict penalties for violations:\n- First-time offenders can face up to 10 years in prison\n- Fines up to \u20b91 lakh\n- Subsequent offenses result in more severe punishments\n\n3. Challenges in implementation:\n- Illegal liquor trade continues\n- Rise in bootlegging and smuggling of alcohol\n- Deaths due to consumption of spurious liquor\n\n4. Impact:\n- Reduced alcohol-related crimes\n- Improved family economic conditions\n- Health benefits\n- Loss of significant revenue for the state\n\n5. Current status:\n- The ban remains in effect\n- Continues to be controversial\n- Some calls for relaxation or modification of the policy\n\nDespite challenges, the Bihar government maintains its strict stance on alcohol prohibition, citing social and economic benefits as justification for the ban.",
